}}'''Afghanistan''' is a country added to BitLife in June 2019. Its three default cities are the capital, Kabul, along with Jalalabad and Kandahar.

== Information ==
Being an Islam-based country, female characters in BitLife will wear hijabs when they are adults. This is shared with females in [[Iran]], [[Iraq]], [[United Arab Emirates|UAE]], or [[Saudi Arabia]]. If a female does not originally have one before emigrating, her emoji will be replaced with one that does. If she emigrates to a non-Islam based country, her hijab may be removed. Female lovers or hook-ups who originate from one of these countries will have her hijab.

On June 9, 2019 on [[IOS version|iOS]]; new countries were added. Along with Afghanistan; there was also [[Belgium]], [[Djibouti]], [[Dominican Republic]], [[Iraq]], [[Poland]], [[Puerto Rico]], [[Switzerland]], [[Taiwan]], [[Thailand]], [[United Arab Emirates]], and [[Uruguay]]. It was added to Android September 21, 2019.

Afghanistan, along with [[Angola]], [[Belize]]. [[El Salvador]], [[Guatemala]], [[Guyana]], [[Haiti]], [[Iraq]], [[Pakistan]], [[Papua New Guinea]], [[Syria]] and [[Venezuela]], are the 12 countries in the game where [[Death|deaths]] are influenced by the country a character is from, in this case, characters can die from unexpected terrorist or battlefield attacks. Being killed by an attack under the age of 30 will give your character the ''Unlucky'' ribbon, making it easier to obtain (though there is a chance that they may end up getting a different ribbon besides ''Unlucky''). [[Family]] members can also die from these as well and it is likely that a parent or parents will die while your character is still very young.

